              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Free-flowing, non-fragile</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Fragile, sluggish, damp</td>
              <td class="py-3">High-value, sticky, batch</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Discharge Completeness</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Good</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4">Very good</td>
              <td class="py-3">Excellent</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="border-b border-border">
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Lift Height</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-200+ ft</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">20-150 ft</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">20-100 ft</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-ink">Relative Cost</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 pr-4 font-mono text-sm">$$$</td>
              <td class="py-3 font-mono text-sm">$$$$</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-4">Capacities depend on bucket size, belt width, and material bulk density. See <a href="/resources/conveyor-cost-guide/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">conveyor cost guide</a> for pricing factors.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Applications -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface" aria-labelledby="apps-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="section-label text-accent mb-4">Applications</div>
      <h2 id="apps-heading" class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-800 text-ink tracking-wide mb-8">
        Bucket Elevator <span class="text-accent">Applications</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="text-lg text-ink-muted leading-relaxed space-y-6">
        <p><strong class="text-ink">Grain handling:</strong> Centrifugal discharge bucket elevators are the standard for grain elevator operations. They lift grain from receiving pits to storage bins, from bins to dryers, from dryers to cleaners, and from cleaners to loadout. A single grain terminal may have 10+ bucket elevators handling different process stages. Elevator capacity ranges from 50 to 5,000+ bushels per hour.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Cement manufacturing:</strong> Heavy-duty chain bucket elevators lift cement clinker, raw meal, and finished cement between grinding, kiln, cooling, and storage stages. Operating temperatures reach 400&deg;F for hot clinker. Abrasion-resistant buckets and chains handle the extremely abrasive cement materials. Lift heights commonly reach 100-200 feet in cement plants.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Food ingredient processing:</strong> Continuous discharge bucket elevators gently lift fragile food products , cereals, snack foods, pet food, coffee beans, and nuts , from processing to <a href="/industries/packaging-line-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">packaging</a>. <a href="/industries/food-conveyors/sanitary/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Sanitary stainless steel construction</a> meets food safety requirements. The gentle continuous discharge minimizes product breakage. Bucket elevators feed weigh scales, baggers, and case packers from overhead positions.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Chemical and mineral processing:</strong> Bucket elevators lift chemical powders, fertilizers, and minerals between reactors, dryers, classifiers, and storage. Material-specific bucket materials (stainless steel, polymer, AR plate) handle corrosive and abrasive conditions. Explosion venting and inerting systems address combustible dust hazards. Bucket elevators feed <a href="/conveyor-types/screw-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">screw conveyors</a> and <a href="/conveyor-types/drag-chain-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">drag chain conveyors</a> at elevation for distribution to downstream processes.</p>

        <p><strong class="text-ink">Recycling and waste processing:</strong> Bucket elevators lift shredded material, sorted recyclables, and processed waste products between processing stages. Heavy-duty designs handle the variable, unpredictable material characteristics common in waste streams. <a href="/conveyor-types/chain-conveyors/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">Chain-type</a> bucket elevators handle the heavy, abrasive materials in recycling operations.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Selection Guide -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-surface-dim bg-dots" aria-labelledby="selection-heading">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
