          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            What is a bucket elevator?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Buckets on a belt or chain loop inside an enclosed casing, lifting bulk material vertically 20-200+ feet. Discharge types: centrifugal (high speed, free-flowing), continuous (gentle, fragile), internal (complete emptying). See our <a href="/conveyor-types/" class="text-accent hover:text-accent-hover font-semibold">conveyor types guide</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            Centrifugal vs continuous discharge , which is better?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Centrifugal for free-flowing, non-fragile materials at high capacity. Continuous for fragile, sluggish, or damp materials needing gentle handling. Centrifugal costs less and delivers higher TPH. Continuous preserves material quality. Match to your material requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group border border-border bg-surface p-6 open:pb-8">
          <summary class="font-display text-xl font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-ink cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between group-open:mb-4">
            How high can a bucket elevator lift?
            <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-ink-muted group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0 ml-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="text-ink-muted leading-relaxed">
            <p>Standard: 20-150 feet. Large industrial: 200+ feet. Belt elevators to 150 ft. Chain elevators to 200+ ft. Lift height determines belt length, casing size, structural support, and drive horsepower. Grain terminals and cement plants use the tallest elevators.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-ink-light" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
